\par enough for this class when it is a question of war! Yet the priests
\par are, as is notorious, _the worst enemies_--why? Because they are the
\par weakest. Their weakness causes their hate to expand into a monstrous
\par and sinister shape, a shape which is most crafty and most poisonous.
\par The really great haters in the history of the world have always been
\par priests, who are also the cleverest haters--in comparison with the
\par cleverness of priestly revenge, every other piece of cleverness is
\par practically negligible. Human history would be too fatuous for anything
\par were it not for the cleverness imported into it by the weak--take at
\par once the most important instance. All the world's efforts against the
\par "aristocrats," the "mighty," the "masters," the "holders of power,"
\par are negligible by comparison with what has been accomplished against
\par those classes by _the Jews_--the Jews, that priestly nation which
\par eventually realised that the one method of effecting satisfaction on
\par its enemies and tyrants was by means of a radical transvaluation of
\par values, which was at the same time an act of the _cleverest revenge_.
